text:
Swisscom AG is Switzerland’s leading telecommunications and information technology company, with a notable presence in Italy through its subsidiary Fastweb. Headquartered in Ittigen, near Bern, Swisscom provides a comprehensive range of services, including mobile and fixed-line telephony, broadband internet, digital television, and various IT services.

The company has a rich history, tracing its origins back to 1851 with the establishment of a state-run telegraph service. Over time, it evolved to include telephone services and was part of the PTT (Post, Telegraph, and Telephone) formed in 1920. In 1997, Swisscom was created as a separate entity from the postal services, and a year later, it was partially privatized.

Swisscom is structured into several key segments: Swisscom Switzerland, offering services to residential and business customers within Switzerland; Fastweb, operating in Italy, providing telecommunications services; and other subsidiaries and brands, including Wingo, Coop Mobile, and M-Budget Mobile.

In 2023, Swisscom employed approximately 19,729 full-time equivalents and reported revenues exceeding 11 billion CHF. It holds significant market shares in Switzerland's telecommunications sector, including 56% in mobile communications, 51% in broadband internet, and 37% in digital television. In Italy, Fastweb holds a 16% market share among private broadband customers and 29% among corporate clients.

Swisscom has shown consistent financial performance with revenues of 11.072 billion CHF, an EBITDA of 4.406 billion CHF, and a net profit of 1.603 billion CHF in 2023. The company is recognized for its innovation and sustainability efforts, focusing on advancing telecommunications technology and reducing environmental impact.

In recent developments, Swisscom announced plans in March 2024 to merge Fastweb with Vodafone Italia to strengthen its position in the Italian market. The Swiss government maintains a controlling interest in Swisscom, underscoring its strategic importance to national infrastructure. Despite competition from other providers like Sunrise and UPC, Swisscom remains a dominant player in the industry.
